  "dateModified": "2018-04-11",
  "datePublished": "2018-04-11",
  "description": "In 2009, as the world was going through a economic recession, Russian social media mogul Yuri Milner invested $200m in Facebook, with a valuation of $10b, without requesting a seat on the board or voting rights.\nThe investment was financed by Alisher B. Usmanov, who provided funds from Gazprom, a Russian natural gas-and-more conglomerate. It\u0026rsquo;s likely the investment is what pushed out Facebook\u0026rsquo;s early CFO Gideon Yu.\nThe investments were facilitated by Ryan Williams, a friend and former classmate of Jared Kushner. At a similar time, Yuri Milner also invested in Cadre, a company founded by Williams, Kushner, and Kushner\u0026rsquo;s brother, Josh Kushner. However, Jared Kushner failed to disclose his ownership of the company.\n",
  "name": "Facebook did not accidentally fail",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Person",
